manual commands
Here are the manual commands to set up Rancher on Ubuntu step by step:

1ï¸âƒ£ Update and Upgrade Ubuntu

sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

2ï¸âƒ£ Install OpenSSH Server

sudo apt install -y openssh-server

3ï¸âƒ£ Install cURL

sudo apt install -y curl

Verify cURL installation:

curl --version

4ï¸âƒ£ Install Required Dependencies for Docker

sudo apt install -y ca-certificates curl gnupg

5ï¸âƒ£ Add Docker GPG Key

sudo install -m 0755 -d /etc/apt/keyrings
curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo tee /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc > /dev/null
sudo chmod a+r /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc

6ï¸âƒ£ Add Docker Repository

echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu $(lsb_release -cs) stable" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null

Update APT Cache:

sudo apt update

7ï¸âƒ£ Install Docker

sudo apt install -y docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-buildx-plugin docker-compose-plugin

Check Docker Version:

docker --version

8ï¸âƒ£ Start and Enable Docker

sudo systemctl enable --now docker

9ï¸âƒ£ Add User to Docker Group

sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
newgrp docker

Verify Docker Works Without Sudo:

docker run hello-world

ğŸ”Ÿ Pull and Run Rancher Docker Container

sudo docker run --privileged -d --restart=unless-stopped -p 80:80 -p 443:443 rancher/rancher

1ï¸âƒ£1ï¸âƒ£ Check if Rancher is Running

docker ps

Expected Output:

You should see a container with the rancher/rancher image running.

1ï¸âƒ£2ï¸âƒ£ Get Rancher Container ID

docker ps --filter "ancestor=rancher/rancher" --format "{{.ID}}"

1ï¸âƒ£3ï¸âƒ£ Get Rancher Bootstrap Password

docker logs $(docker ps --filter "ancestor=rancher/rancher" --format "{{.ID}}") 2>&1 | grep "Bootstrap Password:" | awk '{print $NF}'

1ï¸âƒ£4ï¸âƒ£ Open Rancher in Your Browser

Get the systemâ€™s IP address:

ip -4 a show $(ip route | grep default | awk '{print $5}') | grep inet | awk '{print $2}' | cut -d/ -f1

Then open:

http://<YOUR_SERVER_IP>

or

